IMPORTS

Matplotlib is the most popular plotting package for python. Pandas is a python library used mainly for data manipulation and analysis. Pyplot is a collection of command style functions that enhance the work of matplotlib.NumPy is a python package used for scientific computing.SciPy is a python library used for scientific and technical computing. SciPy basically uses NumPy for more mathematical functions.

import pandas as pd
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import ttest_ind
import numpy as np

Data Visualization

Line Graph

Data Visualization is usually the first step of any work involving data analysis. Creating visualizations really helps in making things clearer and easier to understand.Line charts are best used when you can clearly see that one variable varies greatly with another i.e they have a high covariance. In the first graph, the year associated with the income is plotted on the x-axis while the values associated with the varibale income are plotted on the y-axis while in the second graph,the year associated with the rent is plotted on the x-axis while the values associated with the rent varibale income are plotted on the y-axis

plt.plot (income.year, income.value)
plt.title ("Median Household Income")
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Value")
plt.show()

plt.plot (rent.year, rent.value)
plt.title ("Median Gross Rent")
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Value")
plt.show()

Plotting on same axes

I was further interested in plotting both the variables income and rent on the same chart.The values associated with the variable income were very high compared to the values associated with the rent variable so I divided the income values by 50 to have a more presentable visualization.

plt.plot (income.year, income.value/50)
plt.plot (rent.year, rent.value)
plt.title ("Median Household Income vs Median Gross Rent")
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Value")
plt.legend(["Median Household Income","Median Gross Rent"])
plt.show()

Hypothesis Testing

Using the Scipy library, I carry out a statistics test to find out if the data between the Median Household Income and the Median Household Rent is significant. I use a T-Test of Independece which is the test used for the means of two independent samples. The null hypothesis in my study is that the Median Household Income and the Median Household Rent have identical average values and I'm hoping to either reject or accept it based off the results of my p-value.A p-value helps you determine the significance of your results when you perform a hypothesis test.If we reject the null hypothesis, the results are considered significant.
